---
rule_type: always
---
- Use clear, descriptive variable and function names. Avoid abbreviations.
- Use ES6+ syntax (arrow functions, `const`/`let`, template strings).
- Include comments for non-obvious logic or edge cases.
- Prefer small, single-responsibility functions.
- Use Express.js for API routes (GET/POST).
- Validate API inputs (e.g. check required fields).
- Handle errors with proper status codes and messages.
- Return JSON responses consistently.